            "text": ", the rule that says debt can only be forgiven if the borrower’s financial status is unlikely to improve for a substantial part of the repayment period. If the Supreme Court had agreed with McCoy’s petition for a more lenient “totality of the circumstances” standard, student loan debtors across the country might have found it easier to discharge their student loan debt.",
